==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preterist
<hw>Pret"er*ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>preter-</ets> + <ets>-ist</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One whose
chief interest is in the past; one who regards the past with most
pleasure or favor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>One who believes the prophecies
of the Apocalypse to have been already fulfilled.</def>
<rj><au>Farrar.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preterit</ent>⟦br⟧
